Carrot Cake with Cream Cheese Frosting
  --America's Test Kitchen

Cake:
2 1/2 c ap flour (12 1/2 oz)
1 1/4 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
1 1/4 tsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp nutmeg
1/8 tsp cloves
1/2 tsp salt
1 lb medium carrots (6-7) peeled
1 1/2 c sugar (10 1/2 oz)
1/2 c packed light brown sugar (3 1/2 oz)
4 large eggs
1 1/2 c vegetable oil

Adjust oven rack to middle position; heat to 350F. Spray 13x9" pan with nonstick cooking spray; line bottom with parchment and spray parchment. Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, and salt in large bowl, set aside. In food processor fitted with large shredding disk, shred carrots (should have ~3 c); transfer carrots to bowl and set aside. Wipe out food processor and fit with metal blade. Process granulated and brown sugars and eggs until frothy and thoroughly combined, ~10 s. With machine running, add oil through feed tube in steady stream. Process until mixture is light in color and well emulsified, ~20 s. Scrape mixture into medium bowl. Stir in carrots and dry ingredients until incorporated and no streaks of flour remain. Pour into prepared pan and bake until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, 35-40 min, rotating pan halfway through. cool cake to room temp in pan on wire rack, ~2 hrs.

Frosting:
8 oz cream cheese, softened but still cool
5 tbsp unsalted butter, softened but still cool
1 tbsp sour cream
1/2 tsp vanilla
1/4 c confectioners' sugar (4 1/2 oz)

Process cream cheese, butter, sour cream, and vanilla in clean food processor workbowl until combined, ~5 s, scraping down bowl with rubber spatula as needed. Add sugar and process until smooth, ~10 s. Run paring knife around edge of cake to loosen from pan. Invert cake onto wire rack, peel off parchment, then invert again onto serving platter. Using icing spatula, spread frosting evenly over surface of cake. Cut into squares and serve. Cover and refrigerate leftovers for up to 3 days.
